XtSetMultiClickTime(3)                                                                         XT FUNCTIONS                                                                         XtSetMultiClickTime(3)

NAME
       XtSetMultiClickTime, XtGetMultiClickTime - set and get multi-click times

SYNTAX
       #include <X11/Intrinsic.h>

       void XtSetMultiClickTime(Display* display, int time);

       int XtGetMultiClickTime(Display* display);

ARGUMENTS
       display   Specifies the display connection.

       time      Specifies the multi-click time in milliseconds.

DESCRIPTION
       XtSetMultiClickTime sets the time interval used by the translation manager to determine when multiple events are interpreted as a repeated event.

       XtGetMultiClickTime returns the time in milliseconds that the translation manager uses to determine if multiple events are to be interpreted as a repeated event for purposes of matching a trans‚Äê
       lation entry containing a repeat count.

